collections.name: Keren SouzaKohn RWA Tokens
collections.description: An innovative project is tokenizing 926 artworks by Keren SouzaKohn, an artist in her own right and daughter of the renowned Indian modernist F.N. Souza. Each token represents a 1:1 claim on a physical artwork, pioneering a new model of art ownership and accessibility. With the aim of democratizing art collecting, tokens are initially priced at just 1000 Indian Rupees (approximately 0.005 ETH). High-resolution digital images of the artworks are available for download, allowing collectors to create prints on canvas, paper, metal, and other media. A 5% commission will be applied to all sales. Once the project's floor price reaches 0.5 ETH, token holders can burn their token and redeem it for the corresponding physical artwork. Contact us for details on the redemption process. We also offer opportunities for social media interaction with Keren SouzaKohn, including Q&A sessions and virtual studio tours. Connect with us on Twitter or Discord for more information.

collections.name: Coin of World
collections.description: Increasing digitalization is replacing traditional money, and even more so minted coins.  The Coin of world creative project offers to transfer previously issued and issued coins to nft in order to preserve the opportunity to collect and share your collections with others. In addition, the nft coin will be a great addition to the physical coin and will allow you to roll out and show your collection to many on your phone screen, rather than forcing it to gather dust somewhere on the shelf.

collections.name: Grinch vs Doge
collections.description:
Once upon a time in the bustling digital town of CryptoVille, there lived a mischievous creature named Grinch. He was known for his sour disposition and his disdain for all things cheerful, especially the popular and beloved cryptocurrency, Dogecoin.
Dogecoin, or simply DOGE, was a fun-loving, playful currency that brought joy to everyone it encountered. Its cute Shiba Inu mascot adorned every transaction, making people smile wherever it went. But Grinch hated seeing others happy, so he decided to do something dastardly—he would try to steal some DOGE coins!
One dark and stormy night, when the residents of CryptoVille were fast asleep, Grinch sneaked into the town's blockchain network. He knew that if he could get his hands on just one wallet full of DOGE, he could cause chaos and ruin the festive spirit of the community.
Grinch crept through the virtual streets, avoiding the watchful eyes of miners and validators.

collections.name: Rock The Alpha
collections.description: Screens can’t measure transparency, but we sure can tokenize some of it. There was once a trader whose portfolio was the stuff of legends—except, no one could ever quite figure out what was in it. They say it was a collection of options so cryptic, even the gods couldn’t decide what was really being traded. If you asked him about his portfolio, he’d simply smile and say, “It’s a game. A Paper, Rock, Scissors game, but with more… intent.” He’s been holding these options for centuries and he’s still alpha smiling, probably knowing that it’s not his cryptic assets that keep the business running—it’s everyone else trying to figure them out.
